1
00:01:26,092 --> 00:01:30,826
- IMAGINE,
THE GATEWAY TO THE TOMB
DISGUISED AS A PEARL

2
00:01:30,859 --> 00:01:33,059
WITHIN THE RIGHT EYE
OF INUYASHA.

3
00:01:33,092 --> 00:01:37,992
NO WONDER LORD SESSHOMARU
WAS UNABLE TO FIND IT.

4
00:01:39,126 --> 00:01:41,826
OF COURSE,
NOW THAT HE HAS FOUND IT,

5
00:01:41,859 --> 00:01:44,092
THERE'S NO TIME TO WASTE.

6
00:01:44,126 --> 00:01:48,492
TETSUSAIGA,
SWORD OF ULTIMATE POWER!

7
00:01:50,892 --> 00:01:52,626
THE TIME IS NOW, MILORD.

8
00:01:52,659 --> 00:01:54,826
MAKE IT YOUR OWN!

9
00:01:55,659 --> 00:01:59,826
- DO YOU MEAN TO SAY
INUYASHA CAN?

10
00:01:59,859 --> 00:02:02,759
- SESSHOMARU COULDN'T
PULL IT OUT, RIGHT?

11
00:02:02,792 --> 00:02:04,359
IF YOU CAN'T HIT HIM
IN THE BODY,

12
00:02:04,392 --> 00:02:05,759
HIT HIM IN THE EGO.

13
00:02:05,792 --> 00:02:07,759
HURT HIS PRIDE.

14
00:02:10,059 --> 00:02:11,259
- OH, NO!

15
00:02:11,292 --> 00:02:14,659
INUYASHA IS IMMUNE TO THE SPELL
THAT THWARTED LORD SESSHOMARU.

16
00:02:14,692 --> 00:02:16,492
- I KNEW IT.

17
00:02:16,526 --> 00:02:20,592
TETSUSAIGA IS MEANT
TO BELONG TO LORD INUYASHA.

18
00:02:23,659 --> 00:02:25,592
- PULL HARDER!

19
00:02:27,126 --> 00:02:28,426
- ARE YOU DONE?

20
00:02:28,459 --> 00:02:30,092
I AM.

21
00:02:33,359 --> 00:02:34,892
- INUYASHA!

22
00:02:34,926 --> 00:02:36,426
[GASPS]

23
00:02:37,959 --> 00:02:39,926
UH-OH.

24
00:02:44,126 --> 00:02:45,026
SORRY.

25
00:02:45,059 --> 00:02:46,592
NOW WHAT?

26
00:02:55,659 --> 00:02:57,026
OH.

27
00:02:57,059 --> 00:03:00,026
[GASPING]

28
00:03:00,059 --> 00:03:01,559
- THAT'S IMPOSSIBLE!

29
00:03:01,592 --> 00:03:03,459
IF THE TWO OF THEM
COULDN'T DO IT,

30
00:03:03,492 --> 00:03:06,959
HOW COULD A MERE HUMAN
EVER HOPE TO--

31
00:03:06,992 --> 00:03:08,092
- DON'T LOOK AT HER.

32
00:03:08,126 --> 00:03:10,559
LOOK AT ME!

33
00:03:10,592 --> 00:03:11,492
HUH?

34
00:03:11,526 --> 00:03:13,692
[GASPS]

35
00:03:13,726 --> 00:03:14,426
- WHAT ARE YOU,

36
00:03:14,459 --> 00:03:17,526
AND HOW DID YOU
DRAW THE SWORD?

37
00:03:18,826 --> 00:03:22,159
- GOOD THING
HE'S AFTER HER NOW
AND NOT US,

38
00:03:22,192 --> 00:03:24,426
EH, LORD INUYASHA?

39
00:03:24,459 --> 00:03:25,092
- BE QUIET!

40
00:03:25,126 --> 00:03:26,992
SESSHOMARU,
LEAVE HER ALONE!

41
00:03:27,026 --> 00:03:29,092
SHE'S NOT INVOLVED IN THIS.

42
00:03:29,126 --> 00:03:29,992
- INUYASHA!

43
00:03:30,026 --> 00:03:32,526
ONE STEP CLOSER,
AND I'LL CUT YOU.

44
00:03:32,559 --> 00:03:34,359
- FOR SOME UNKNOWN REASON,

45
00:03:34,392 --> 00:03:36,559
I WAS UNABLE
TO DRAW TETSUSAIGA.

46
00:03:36,592 --> 00:03:40,059
FORTUNATELY,
YOU WERE UNABLE
TO DRAW IT EITHER.

47
00:03:40,092 --> 00:03:43,026
IT'S OBVIOUS
THAT SHE MUST DIE.

48
00:03:43,059 --> 00:03:43,992
- YOU'RE RIGHT,

49
00:03:44,026 --> 00:03:45,326
IT IS WEIRD
SHE COULD DO IT
AND WE COULDN'T,

50
00:03:45,359 --> 00:03:47,826
BUT SHE'S STILL
JUST A HUMAN GIRL.

51
00:03:47,859 --> 00:03:49,992
KAGOME, GIVE HIM THE SWORD.

52
00:03:50,026 --> 00:03:51,292
THERE'S NO CHOICE.

53
00:03:51,326 --> 00:03:52,192
- NO WAY.

54
00:03:52,226 --> 00:03:54,159
WHY DOES HE AUTOMATICALLY
GET TO KEEP IT?

55
00:03:54,192 --> 00:03:55,759
IF HE COULDN'T PULL IT OUT,

56
00:03:55,792 --> 00:03:57,359
IT MEANS HE'S NOT
SUPPOSED TO HAVE IT.

57
00:03:57,392 --> 00:03:59,326
HE'LL HAVE TO
COME AND TAKE IT.

58
00:03:59,359 --> 00:04:00,292
- DON'T BE STUPID.

59
00:04:00,326 --> 00:04:01,126
YOU'RE ONLY A HUMAN,

60
00:04:01,159 --> 00:04:04,192
SO BACK OFF, SHUT UP,
AND BUTT OUT.

61
00:04:04,226 --> 00:04:05,092
- BUTT OUT?

62
00:04:05,126 --> 00:04:06,126
WHAT DO YOU KNOW?

63
00:04:06,159 --> 00:04:07,826
YOU'RE JUST A--

64
00:04:07,859 --> 00:04:09,159
OOH!

65
00:04:09,192 --> 00:04:12,659
- INUYASHA, YOUR PATIENCE
WITH THIS CREATURE
IS ASTONISHING TO ME.

66
00:04:12,692 --> 00:04:16,692
YOU PROTECT HER,
INDULGE HER--

67
00:04:16,726 --> 00:04:18,926
EVEN SEEM TO LOVE HER.

68
00:04:18,959 --> 00:04:21,459
- UH...

69
00:04:23,459 --> 00:04:26,192
- CERTAINLY THESE
FEELINGS OF MERCY OF YOURS

70
00:04:26,226 --> 00:04:32,126
ARE NOT SOMETHING
I INHERITED FROM OUR GREAT
AND TERRIBLE FATHER.

71
00:04:35,026 --> 00:04:36,992
IT MUST HAVE BEEN
THAT MOTHER OF YOURS--

72
00:04:37,026 --> 00:04:42,192
THAT HUMAN MOTHER
WHO CAUSED OUR FATHER
TO MEET HIS END

73
00:04:42,226 --> 00:04:45,126
IN THIS IGNOBLE PLACE.

74
00:04:47,192 --> 00:04:50,326
HER BLOOD AFFECTS YOU
AS WELL.

75
00:04:50,359 --> 00:04:54,492
IS IT THAT WHICH
SO ENDEARS YOU TO THEM?

76
00:04:54,526 --> 00:04:55,392
WHEN IT COMES TO HUMANS,

77
00:04:55,426 --> 00:04:59,792
I, OF COURSE,
BEAR NO SUCH WEAKNESS.

78
00:05:03,026 --> 00:05:04,792
[WHIMPERS]

79
00:05:04,826 --> 00:05:07,392
- INUYASHA!

80
00:05:09,026 --> 00:05:11,559
- KAGOME!

81
00:05:19,292 --> 00:05:22,759
- SO FRAGILE,
DON'T YOU AGREE,
LITTLE BROTHER?

82
00:05:22,792 --> 00:05:23,726
- SESSHOMARU.

83
00:05:23,759 --> 00:05:27,726
- AND NOT JUST HUMANS--
HALF-BREEDS, TOO.

84
00:05:30,226 --> 00:05:33,726
- IRON REAPER SOUL STEALER!

85
00:05:35,092 --> 00:05:37,959
- HOW CAN YOU THINK
WITH YOUR DIRTY BLOOD

86
00:05:37,992 --> 00:05:40,559
THAT YOU ARE MY EQUAL?

87
00:05:47,726 --> 00:05:50,226
- YOU...

88
00:05:54,159 --> 00:06:00,059
- YOU FORGET YOUR STATION,
WORTHLESS HALF-BREED.

89
00:06:04,092 --> 00:06:06,826
- A HALF-BREED, AM I?

90
00:06:08,692 --> 00:06:11,326
[MEN CHUCKLING]

91
00:06:42,926 --> 00:06:45,492
HALF-BREED?

92
00:06:56,159 --> 00:06:57,826
MOTHER!

93
00:06:59,292 --> 00:07:02,959
WHAT'S A HALF-BREED?

94
00:07:02,992 --> 00:07:04,159
THAT'S RIGHT.

95
00:07:04,192 --> 00:07:06,259
I REMEMBER.

96
00:07:09,226 --> 00:07:12,959
MY MOTHER,
SHE WAS CRYING--

97
00:07:12,992 --> 00:07:14,426
CRYING FOR ME.

98
00:07:14,459 --> 00:07:18,759
SHE KNEW WHAT IT MEANT,
WHAT MY LIFE WOULD BE LIKE.

99
00:07:27,526 --> 00:07:31,459
HALF-BREED OR FULL-BREED,
TO ME IT DON'T MATTER.

100
00:07:31,492 --> 00:07:33,292
BUT WHEN YOU
INSULT MY MOTHER,

101
00:07:33,326 --> 00:07:35,926
THAT'S WHEN I GET ANGRY.

102
00:07:36,426 --> 00:07:39,792
FOR HER SAKE THEN,
IF NOTHING ELSE,

103
00:07:39,826 --> 00:07:42,759
I'M GONNA MAKE YOU PAY.

104
00:07:44,226 --> 00:07:45,459
THAT WAS FOR MOTHER,

105
00:07:45,492 --> 00:07:49,759
AND THIS--
THIS IS FOR KAGOME.

106
00:07:57,126 --> 00:07:58,692
- THIS CAN'T BE HAPPENING.

107
00:07:58,726 --> 00:08:01,759
A MOMENT AGO
HE COULDN'T HIT AT ALL.

108
00:08:09,792 --> 00:08:13,492
- ALL THAT FOR A MEMORY
AND A DEAD MORTAL GIRL?

109
00:08:13,526 --> 00:08:16,992
IF I'D KNOWN
THAT'S WHAT IT TOOK
TO MAKE YOU FIGHT,

110
00:08:17,026 --> 00:08:19,959
I'D HAVE KILLED HER SOONER.

111
00:08:19,992 --> 00:08:21,526
- I'M GONNA SLIT YOUR STOMACH,

112
00:08:21,559 --> 00:08:24,559
TAKE OUT YOUR GUTS,
AND PUT 'EM IN A BOWL.

113
00:08:24,592 --> 00:08:25,859
BY THE TIME I'M THROUGH,

114
00:08:25,892 --> 00:08:29,192
YOU'RE GONNA WISH
IT WAS YOU WHO WAS DEAD.

115
00:08:31,392 --> 00:08:33,192
- I THOUGHT I WAS A GONER.

116
00:08:33,226 --> 00:08:34,859
- HUH?

117
00:08:37,126 --> 00:08:37,859
- HEY, YOU!

118
00:08:37,892 --> 00:08:39,892
YOU TRIED TO KILL ME,
DIDN'T YOU?

119
00:08:39,926 --> 00:08:43,792
DON'T GO THINKING
YOU'RE GONNA GET
AWAY WITH IT, MISTER.

120
00:08:43,826 --> 00:08:47,159
HERE. I THINK
WE UNDERESTIMATED IT.

121
00:08:47,192 --> 00:08:48,092
DON'T LET ME DOWN.

122
00:08:48,126 --> 00:08:51,226
- HEY, UH,
HOW COME YOU'RE STILL ALIVE?

123
00:08:51,259 --> 00:08:53,226
- MMM. UH, I DON'T KNOW.

124
00:08:53,259 --> 00:08:58,592
- THE SWORD--
THAT'S WHAT PROTECTED YOU.

125
00:08:58,626 --> 00:08:59,792
- IT'S TRUE.

126
00:08:59,826 --> 00:09:02,326
THOSE CLAWS OF HIS
ARE DEADLY POISON.

127
00:09:02,359 --> 00:09:03,559
IT HAD TO BE THE SWORD,

128
00:09:03,592 --> 00:09:05,226
OR SHE REALLY WOULD HAVE DIED.

129
00:09:05,259 --> 00:09:09,926
WHY NOT PUT IT TO A REAL TEST
AND TRY IT ON SESSHOMARU?

130
00:09:09,959 --> 00:09:13,626
- BIG WORDS
FOR SUCH SMALL VERMIN.

131
00:09:28,226 --> 00:09:29,692
- WHAT'S HIS PROBLEM?

132
00:09:29,726 --> 00:09:30,859
WHAT A JERK.

133
00:09:30,892 --> 00:09:35,459
- LET'S SEE IF A HALF-BREED
CAN EVEN WIELD THE TETSUSAIGA.

134
00:09:38,259 --> 00:09:41,792
I MYSELF SHALL BE THE WITNESS.

135
00:10:10,692 --> 00:10:11,526
- HE CHANGED.

136
00:10:11,559 --> 00:10:15,292
- GOOD, 'CAUSE NOW
WE KNOW HIS REAL FORM.

137
00:10:19,026 --> 00:10:20,959
HEH.

138
00:10:23,126 --> 00:10:23,992
HEH HEH.

139
00:10:24,026 --> 00:10:27,459
NOW THAT I'M USING THIS,
I'LL WIN FOR SURE.

140
00:10:28,959 --> 00:10:35,159
- YUP, I'D SAY THIS BATTLE'S
JUST ABOUT FINISHED
BEFORE IT EVEN STARTS.

141
00:10:35,192 --> 00:10:36,626
HA!

142
00:10:37,892 --> 00:10:40,026
YOU GO HIDE
UNTIL IT'S OVER.

143
00:10:40,059 --> 00:10:42,526
- OK, SURE. BUT WHERE?

144
00:10:42,559 --> 00:10:44,259
- HERE GOES.

145
00:10:44,292 --> 00:10:45,226
THIS IS IT, SWORD.

146
00:10:45,259 --> 00:10:48,459
TIME TO SHOW ME
WHAT YOU'RE MADE OF.

147
00:10:50,326 --> 00:10:52,126
- AAH!

148
00:10:55,592 --> 00:10:57,992
- DIDN'T EVEN MAKE A SCRATCH.

149
00:10:58,026 --> 00:10:59,459
HUH?

150
00:11:13,892 --> 00:11:16,326
YO, MYOGA, WHAT'S THE DEAL?

151
00:11:16,359 --> 00:11:17,926
THIS SWORD CAN'T EVEN BRUISE,

152
00:11:17,959 --> 00:11:18,726
LET ALONE CUT.

153
00:11:18,759 --> 00:11:20,026
- WELL, UH, LORD INUYASHA,

154
00:11:20,059 --> 00:11:24,926
I SUPPOSE THAT, UH,
IT'LL MAKE A LOVELY HEIRLOOM
IF NOTHING ELSE.

155
00:11:24,959 --> 00:11:27,059
BESIDES,
IT'S THE THOUGHT
THAT COUNTS.

156
00:11:27,092 --> 00:11:28,692
NOW, IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME.

157
00:11:28,726 --> 00:11:29,759
- HEY, HEY! WHOA!

158
00:11:29,792 --> 00:11:34,226
- AND DON'T LET THAT SESSHOMARU
PUSH YOU AROUND, OK?

159
00:11:40,392 --> 00:11:41,426
- UH-OH.

160
00:11:41,459 --> 00:11:42,792
KAGOME, QUICK!

161
00:11:42,826 --> 00:11:44,126
GET UP OFF THE GROUND!

162
00:11:44,159 --> 00:11:46,226
- WHAT DO YOU SUGGEST?

163
00:11:46,259 --> 00:11:47,526
- JUST CLIMB UP.

164
00:11:47,559 --> 00:11:49,559
UP! UP!

165
00:12:02,426 --> 00:12:03,292
- INUYASHA!

166
00:12:03,326 --> 00:12:05,226
- NOW JUST CLIMB!

167
00:12:05,259 --> 00:12:08,959
EVEN A DEMON CAN'T STAY
IN THOSE FUMES FOR LONG.

168
00:12:08,992 --> 00:12:11,359
- LORD SESSHOMARU, I CAN'T--

169
00:12:11,392 --> 00:12:12,792
AAH!

170
00:12:12,826 --> 00:12:14,092
- WHAT ABOUT HIM?

171
00:12:14,126 --> 00:12:15,859
WHAT ABOUT INUYASHA?

172
00:12:15,892 --> 00:12:17,359
WILL HE BE OK?

173
00:12:17,392 --> 00:12:20,659
- UH, PROBABLY NOT, HUH?

174
00:12:22,626 --> 00:12:24,959
FORGET THE HEROICS.

175
00:12:24,992 --> 00:12:26,959
IT'S EVERY FLEA FOR HIMSELF.

176
00:12:26,992 --> 00:12:28,059
COME ON!

177
00:12:28,092 --> 00:12:30,326
- INUYASHA!

178
00:12:38,492 --> 00:12:39,426
[COUGHS]

179
00:12:39,459 --> 00:12:42,992
- EVEN I CAN'T STAY DOWN HERE
TOO MUCH LONGER.

180
00:12:50,659 --> 00:12:52,159
[COUGHS]

181
00:12:53,526 --> 00:12:56,826
MY ARMS AND LEGS
ARE GOING NUMB.

182
00:13:00,559 --> 00:13:02,992
AAH!

183
00:13:14,426 --> 00:13:15,959
EVEN A MOSQUITO
WITH WOODEN TEETH

184
00:13:15,992 --> 00:13:19,259
MUST BITE HARDER
THAN THIS PIECE OF JUNK.

185
00:13:20,826 --> 00:13:22,759
AAH!

186
00:13:29,526 --> 00:13:31,426
- INUYASHA!

187
00:13:56,637 --> 00:13:58,837
- NOW DO YOU SEE
THE POWER OF TETSUSAIGA?

188
00:13:58,871 --> 00:14:02,037
OH, YOU'RE GIVING
SESSHOMARU WHAT FOR, I HOPE.

189
00:14:02,071 --> 00:14:02,804
WOO-HOO!

190
00:14:02,837 --> 00:14:03,804
- WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

191
00:14:03,837 --> 00:14:06,037
THIS THING'S ABOUT AS USEFUL
AS A WALKING STICK!

192
00:14:06,071 --> 00:14:10,171
- OH, SO MAYBE
IT ISN'T FROM YOUR FATHER.

193
00:14:10,204 --> 00:14:13,004
[CLEARS THROAT]

194
00:14:13,037 --> 00:14:13,971
- HEY!

195
00:14:14,004 --> 00:14:15,671
HE LEFT.

196
00:14:15,704 --> 00:14:16,804
- WHY AM I NOT SURPRISED?

197
00:14:16,837 --> 00:14:21,004
IN THE MEANTIME,
WHAT AM I GONNA DO
WITH THIS THING?

198
00:14:30,604 --> 00:14:31,337
- THAT'S IT!

199
00:14:31,371 --> 00:14:32,671
SOCK IT TO HIM, INUYASHA!

200
00:14:32,704 --> 00:14:34,237
I THINK THE FIRST ONE HIT.

201
00:14:34,271 --> 00:14:35,204
- WHAT, ARE YOU NUTS?

202
00:14:35,237 --> 00:14:36,637
THAT WASN'T EVEN CLOSE.

203
00:14:36,671 --> 00:14:38,304
- BUT THE SWORD'S YOURS NOW.

204
00:14:38,337 --> 00:14:40,571
ALL YOU GOTTA DO
IS BELIEVE IN IT--

205
00:14:40,604 --> 00:14:42,837
LIKE I BELIEVE IN YOU.

206
00:14:45,537 --> 00:14:46,704
- YOU ARE NUTS.

207
00:14:46,737 --> 00:14:48,537
THIS SWORD
IS GOOD FOR NOTHING.

208
00:14:48,571 --> 00:14:49,671
ME, I'LL LIVE.

209
00:14:49,704 --> 00:14:51,071
I'M HALF DEMON.

210
00:14:51,104 --> 00:14:51,871
YOU, THOUGH?

211
00:14:51,904 --> 00:14:53,104
YOU AIN'T GOT A CHANCE.

212
00:14:53,137 --> 00:14:55,804
- SO I SHOULD JUST...
GIVE UP HOPE?

213
00:14:55,837 --> 00:14:59,471
- WHAT--WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

214
00:14:59,504 --> 00:15:02,437
YOU'RE NOT CRYING, ARE YOU?

215
00:15:02,471 --> 00:15:03,904
NO CRYING!

216
00:15:03,937 --> 00:15:04,904
- OH, SHOULD I LAUGH?

217
00:15:04,937 --> 00:15:08,737
- NO, YOU SHOULD SHUT UP
AND LET ME PROTECT YOU.

218
00:15:08,771 --> 00:15:10,437
[GASPS]

219
00:15:12,504 --> 00:15:15,771
- HEH. YOU STAY HERE
AND WATCH.

220
00:15:19,337 --> 00:15:20,171
- WAIT A SEC.

221
00:15:20,204 --> 00:15:22,437
I DIDN'T IMAGINE THAT,
DID I?

222
00:15:22,471 --> 00:15:25,537
DID HE JUST SAY
HE'D PROTECT ME?

223
00:15:25,571 --> 00:15:28,337
IN SOME WAYS
HE IS LIKE HIS BROTHER,

224
00:15:28,371 --> 00:15:32,437
BUT IN OTHERS
HE'S TOTALLY DIFFERENT.

225
00:15:36,337 --> 00:15:37,037
- YEAH, YEAH.

226
00:15:37,071 --> 00:15:39,304
ROAR, ROAR,
TO YOU, TOO, BUDDY.

227
00:15:39,337 --> 00:15:41,271
LET'S GET IT OVER WITH.

228
00:15:41,304 --> 00:15:43,937
[HEART BEATING]

229
00:15:45,504 --> 00:15:46,671
HUH?

230
00:15:46,704 --> 00:15:49,104
TETSUSAIGA IS PULSING.

231
00:15:49,137 --> 00:15:50,671
I CAN HEAR IT--

232
00:15:50,704 --> 00:15:52,471
THE SOUND FROM BEFORE.

233
00:15:52,504 --> 00:15:55,571
NO, THIS TIME
IT'S DIFFERENT.

234
00:15:55,604 --> 00:15:57,437
- GET HIM, LORD SESSHOMARU!

235
00:15:57,471 --> 00:15:58,971
BITE HIS LITTLE HEAD OFF!

236
00:15:59,004 --> 00:15:59,771
THAT'S RIGHT!

237
00:15:59,804 --> 00:16:01,104
NIBBLE OF HIS LITTLE--OW!

238
00:16:01,137 --> 00:16:03,404
- WE'LL SEE WHO EATS WHO.

239
00:16:03,437 --> 00:16:05,537
- D'OH!

240
00:16:05,571 --> 00:16:06,704
- YOU CAN DO IT.

241
00:16:06,737 --> 00:16:08,704
I JUST KNOW IT.

242
00:16:13,904 --> 00:16:15,871
- NOW.

243
00:16:25,637 --> 00:16:28,704
IT LOOKS LIKE A BANG.

244
00:16:36,337 --> 00:16:37,237
[CHUCKLES]

245
00:16:37,271 --> 00:16:38,304
IT IS A BANG.

246
00:16:38,337 --> 00:16:42,704
THE OLD MAN
REALLY DID LEAVE
SOMETHING WORTHWHILE.

247
00:16:46,071 --> 00:16:46,937
SO HERE WE ARE,

248
00:16:46,971 --> 00:16:49,837
TWO BROTHERS FIGHTING OVER
FATHER'S SWORD.

249
00:16:49,871 --> 00:16:54,537
BUT COMPARED TO HIM,
YOU AND ME ARE NOTHING.

250
00:16:57,037 --> 00:16:58,137
DON'T YOU GET IT?

251
00:16:58,171 --> 00:17:00,637
WE'RE LIKE A COUPLE OF FLEAS
JUMPING AROUND ON HIS BODY.

252
00:17:00,671 --> 00:17:05,537
HUH. WE'D BE LUCKY
IF HE DIDN'T SQUASH US FLAT.

253
00:17:10,404 --> 00:17:13,137
SO MAYBE I DON'T HAVE
TOO MANY MEMORIES OF HIM,

254
00:17:13,171 --> 00:17:17,837
BUT IT WAS ME
FATHER CHOSE TO HIDE
HIS TOMB IN, AFTER ALL.

255
00:17:17,871 --> 00:17:21,371
I'D RATHER GIVE UP AN EYE
THAN GIVE UP HIS SWORD.

256
00:17:21,404 --> 00:17:25,471
MAYBE I'M NOT SO WORTHLESS
THEN, AM I?

257
00:17:38,304 --> 00:17:40,971
- LORD SESSHOMARU!

258
00:17:45,837 --> 00:17:48,137
DON'T LEAVE ME!

259
00:17:48,904 --> 00:17:50,804
- INUYASHA?

260
00:17:51,904 --> 00:17:54,071
INUYASHA, ARE YOU OK?

261
00:17:54,104 --> 00:17:55,771
[CHUCKLES]

262
00:17:55,804 --> 00:17:56,837
- I TAKE IT BACK.

263
00:17:56,871 --> 00:17:59,504
SO THE SWORD'S NOT
SUCH A PIECE OF JUNK.

264
00:17:59,537 --> 00:18:02,237
- YOU SEE? I WAS RIGHT.

265
00:18:02,271 --> 00:18:04,537
OF COURSE,
IF YOU'D LISTENED EARLIER,

266
00:18:04,571 --> 00:18:05,971
YOU'D NEVER HAVE--

267
00:18:06,004 --> 00:18:08,637
WAIT. OVER THERE. SEE?

268
00:18:08,671 --> 00:18:10,471
I WASN'T RUNNING AWAY.

269
00:18:10,504 --> 00:18:12,804
I WAS GETTING US
A RIDE HOME.

270
00:18:12,837 --> 00:18:15,037
YOU BELIEVE ME, RIGHT?

271
00:18:15,071 --> 00:18:17,971
- OH, SO THEN
YOU DIDN'T RUN AWAY?

272
00:18:18,004 --> 00:18:19,904
- I DIDN'T?

273
00:18:22,271 --> 00:18:23,637
OK, I ADMIT IT.

274
00:18:23,671 --> 00:18:25,037
I RAN AWAY.

275
00:18:25,071 --> 00:18:26,537
BUT YOU HAVE TO BELIEVE ME,

276
00:18:26,571 --> 00:18:28,471
IF I'D KNOWN
YOU'D MAKE A COMEBACK,

277
00:18:28,504 --> 00:18:30,471
I WOULD NEVER
HAVE LEFT YOU.

278
00:18:30,504 --> 00:18:32,571
I'M ASHAMED OF MYSELF.

279
00:18:32,604 --> 00:18:34,637
I OUGHTA HAVE MORE FAITH.

280
00:18:34,671 --> 00:18:36,704
PLEASE--
PLEASE, FORGIVE ME!

281
00:18:36,737 --> 00:18:39,337
IF ONLY I COULD
MAKE IT UP TO YOU.

282
00:18:39,371 --> 00:18:41,571
- MYOGA...

283
00:18:43,004 --> 00:18:43,971
- OH, WELL.

284
00:18:44,004 --> 00:18:47,404
SUCH IS A FLEA'S
LOT IN LIFE.

285
00:19:08,904 --> 00:19:10,537
- SO, HOW ARE YOU DOING?

286
00:19:10,571 --> 00:19:12,404
- ACTUALLY,
I FEEL PRETTY OK.

287
00:19:12,437 --> 00:19:14,871
EVERYTHING'S
BACK TO NORMAL.

288
00:19:14,904 --> 00:19:15,804
AND AT LEAST NOW I KNOW

289
00:19:15,837 --> 00:19:19,171
THAT THE OLD MAN
CAN REST IN PEACE.

290
00:19:21,537 --> 00:19:23,804
- BUT HOW IS IT
THAT YE, CHILD,

291
00:19:23,837 --> 00:19:25,537
WERE ABLE TO PULL
THE TETSUSAIGA?

292
00:19:25,571 --> 00:19:30,837
I MUST SAY,
YE CONTINUE TO SURPRISE ME.

293
00:19:30,871 --> 00:19:31,937
- HMM.

294
00:19:31,971 --> 00:19:34,971
- MY THEORY
IS THAT IT IS BECAUSE
KAGOME IS MORTAL.

295
00:19:35,004 --> 00:19:40,571
DON'T FORGET,
TETSUSAIGA WAS FORGED BY
LORD INUYASHA'S FATHER

296
00:19:40,604 --> 00:19:43,271
AS A WAY TO PROTECT
HIS MORTAL MOTHER.

297
00:19:43,304 --> 00:19:45,871
IT WAS HIS FEELINGS
TOWARDS MORTALS

298
00:19:45,904 --> 00:19:50,404
THAT ALLOWED LORD INUYASHA
TO WIELD IT EFFECTIVELY.

299
00:19:50,437 --> 00:19:54,671
- NO, YOU SHOULD SHUT UP
AND LET ME PROTECT YOU.

300
00:19:54,704 --> 00:19:55,437
- YOU'RE RIGHT.

301
00:19:55,471 --> 00:19:58,004
THAT'S WHEN THE SWORD REACTED.

302
00:19:59,237 --> 00:20:02,171
- TETSUSAIGA IS PULSING.

303
00:20:09,104 --> 00:20:13,604
- FOR SOMEONE LIKE SESSHOMARU
WHO COULD ONLY HATE HUMANS,

304
00:20:13,637 --> 00:20:17,304
WIELDING TETSUSAIGA
WAS IMPOSSIBLE.

305
00:20:17,337 --> 00:20:19,404
- 'TIS A STRANGE STORY, AYE.

306
00:20:19,437 --> 00:20:24,104
TO INUYASHA,
HIS HALF-HUMAN HERITAGE
HAS BEEN A CURSE.

307
00:20:24,137 --> 00:20:28,104
HIS FEELINGS FOR HIS MOTHER
HAVE BEEN TINGED WITH SHAME.

308
00:20:28,137 --> 00:20:32,137
AND YET, THOSE SAME FEELINGS
ARE WHAT MAKE HIM DIFFERENT.

309
00:20:32,171 --> 00:20:36,737
THAT IS WHY HIS FATHER CHOSE HIM
FOR HIS RESTING PLACE.

310
00:20:36,771 --> 00:20:39,671
PERHAPS THE ONE
WHO MOST RESEMBLES
THE FATHER

311
00:20:39,704 --> 00:20:43,671
IS NOT SESSHOMARU,
BUT INUYASHA.

312
00:20:45,037 --> 00:20:47,137
- HMM.

313
00:20:47,171 --> 00:20:48,671
[CLANG]

314
00:20:51,504 --> 00:20:52,337
I SPOKE TOO SOON.

315
00:20:52,371 --> 00:20:55,071
NOW IT'S BACK
TO BEING A PIECE OF JUNK.

316
00:20:55,104 --> 00:20:56,637
- INUYASHA?

317
00:20:56,671 --> 00:20:57,304
- WHAT?

318
00:20:57,337 --> 00:20:58,171
- DO YOU WANT ME TO TELL YOU?

319
00:20:58,204 --> 00:21:00,137
YOU KNOW,
HOW TO USE TETSUSAIGA?

320
00:21:00,171 --> 00:21:02,371
- AND SINCE WHEN
ARE YOU AN EXPERT?

321
00:21:02,404 --> 00:21:07,604
- WELL, DO YOU PROMISE
YOU'LL PROTECT ME WITH IT
FOREVER AND EVER?

322
00:21:07,637 --> 00:21:08,504
- HUH?

323
00:21:08,537 --> 00:21:10,737
WHAT IN THE WORLD
ARE YOU BABBLING ABOUT?

324
00:21:10,771 --> 00:21:12,437
YOUR BRAIN'S BROKEN
OR SOMETHING.

325
00:21:12,471 --> 00:21:15,504
- BUT YOU SAID
I SHOULD LET YOU PROTECT ME!

326
00:21:15,537 --> 00:21:17,337
- I DIDN'T MEAN IT
LIKE THAT!

327
00:21:17,371 --> 00:21:19,371
IF YOU'LL SHUT UP FOR A MINUTE,

328
00:21:19,404 --> 00:21:21,204
I'LL TELL YOU
WHAT A SWORD LIKE THIS

329
00:21:21,237 --> 00:21:23,071
SHOULD REALLY
BE USED FOR.

330
00:21:23,104 --> 00:21:25,737
STUFF LIKE
COLLECTING JEWEL SHARDS

331
00:21:25,771 --> 00:21:27,637
AND MAKING ME MORE POWERFUL.

332
00:21:27,671 --> 00:21:29,504
I SURE AS HECK
AIN'T WASTING IT

333
00:21:29,537 --> 00:21:33,737
ON BABY-SITTING A HELPLESS
LITTLE HUMAN LIKE YOU.

334
00:21:33,771 --> 00:21:35,271
- HMPH!

335
00:21:37,437 --> 00:21:39,071
- I DON'T GET IT.

336
00:21:39,104 --> 00:21:40,771
- HMPH!

337
00:21:43,237 --> 00:21:44,771
SIT, BOY.

338
00:21:45,471 --> 00:21:46,704
IT'S MY FAULT FOR THINKING

339
00:21:46,737 --> 00:21:49,737
I COULD TEACH AN OLD DOG
A NEW TRICK.

340
00:21:49,771 --> 00:21:52,104
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN "TRICK"?

341
00:21:52,137 --> 00:21:54,104
WAIT! WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

342
00:21:54,137 --> 00:21:55,071
COME BACK HERE!

343
00:21:55,104 --> 00:21:59,104
YOU SAID YOU'D TELL ME
HOW TO USE THE SWORD!

344
00:22:09,877 --> 00:22:13,710
[WOMAN SINGING IN JAPANESE]

345
00:23:40,110 --> 00:23:42,243
- SESSHOMARU'S DOWN,
BUT HE'S NOT OUT.

346
00:23:42,276 --> 00:23:46,676
PLUS, HIS LEFT ARM
IS STILL INSIDE
THEIR FATHER'S TOMB.

347
00:23:49,010 --> 00:23:50,976
NOW THAT INUYASHA
HAS TETSUSAIGA,

348
00:23:51,010 --> 00:23:53,710
THE SEARCH FOR MORE
JEWEL SHARDS CONTINUES.

349
00:23:53,743 --> 00:23:55,910
THEY'LL BE A TOWN,
SOME KIDNAPPED GIRLS,

350
00:23:55,943 --> 00:24:00,176
AND A YOUNG SAMURAI
TRYING TO SAVE THE PRINCESS.

351
00:24:00,176 --> 00:24:03,059
NEXT TIME...

352
00:24:03,059 --> 00:24:04,059
SEE YOU SOON!

